The Great Admirals
William Morrow and Company | 1977 | ISBN 0688031838 | Eng | 280 pag | PDF | 30.3 MB

The art of the admiral has always been one of the major influences that shape the course of naval history. In The Great Admirals Richard Hough has set the careers of twenty-one of the great commanders of maritime history within their historical contexts. His book spans five centuries of constantly changing warfare, from the Christian-Moslem struggles of the late Middle Ages to the Pacific battles of World War II
